<h2>Introduction:</h2>
This lab exercises the ability to:
<ul>
    <li>Use predefined JavaScript Functions to solve problems.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Lab Assignment:</h2>

<ol>
    <li> Create a new directory, <b><tt>Lab3</tt></b>, in your class account directory.</li>
    <li> Move into your Lab3 directory</li>
    <li> Using a syntax-highlighting editor, open a new file to edit.  Save it as <tt>Lab3.html</tt>.</li>
    <li> For each of the following tasks,</li>
    <ol>
	<li> modify your Web page file via the editor</li>
	<li> save the file</li>
	<li> refresh the browser open to your Web page</li>
	<li> verify that your modifications did what you've intended</li>
    </ol>
</ol>
<dl>
    <dt><b>Task</b> - Perform <i>all</i> of the requirements in <u>Exercise 4.9</u> in Reed.
    <dd>This kind of interactive story is also known as a
    <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mad_Libs">MadLib</a></i>.
    <dd>Prompt for all missing words before you begin to display the story.
    <dd>Use the term for what you are prompting for as a default value in each case (e.g. the default value would be "<i>animal</i>" if you are prompting for an animal).
    <dd>Additionally, prompt for at least one of each of the following:
    <ul>
	<li>noun
	<li>adjective (<i>modifies a noun</i>)
	<li>verb
	<li>adverb (<i>modifies a verb</i>)
    </ul>
</dl>
    <p>
When finished (after you’ve proofread your Web page), submit your file to the appropriate D2L dropbox.
